      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PENNY BLACK NZ (8) is a smart mare who had to work when racing parked but proved too strong first up, digging deep to get home at this circuit and distance. Draws wider but has won three of five second-up attempts so should be improved. Can go on with it. LITTLE DARLING (9) has some ground to make up on Penny Black through last week's fourth but she did a good job to come from this barrier for a resuming win prior. Race fit now and worth another chance. HUNGER STRIKE (3) has had four weeks off since she came from the back row for fourth over a shorter trip at G3 level. Had put together a string of wins and placings at this circuit and distance prior. Contender. MADAM PUBLISHER NZ (6) could be close to a win following a narrow second to Penny Black last week.",
